<TITLE> AL won't accept delayed polls </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 8 (bdnews24.com)Taking up his new role as party spokesperson Awami League joint general secretary Syed Ashraful Islam said Saturday AL would not accept deferment of Jatiya Sangsad elections. "The election must be held on Dec 18. There is no need for pushing them back," Ashraf said at the conclusion of a three-day central working committee meeting at the party president's political office at Dhanmondi Saturday evening. "We do not want deferral of election. After today's meeting we ask the nation to remain vigilant to protect democracy." Also speaking in Gazipur Saturday, Ashraf said: "If, due to the actions of some, the election is not held, the chaos of anarchy will prevail." Such a situation may give rise to a take over by "autocratic forces", he warned. Back in Dhaka, Ashraf told reporters after the CWC meeting that Awami League's nomination board had been recast and an election steering committee formed. His name has been included with those who were previously appointed to the nomination board, said the joint general secretary. Prior to the scrapped election of Jan 22, 2007 the nomination board included AL president Sheikh Hasina, Syeda Sajeda Chowdhury, Amir Hossain Amu, Abdur Razzak, Tofail Ahmed, Abdul Jalil, Suranjit Sengupta, Kazi Zafarullah, Mohiuddin Khan Alamgir, Obaidul Quader and Prof Alauddin Ahmed. Hasina will chair AL's election steering committee has been formed with as its chairman. Former cabinet secretary HT Imam has been made co-chairman, while Ashraf will be member secretary. The committee will also include the AL central working committee members and members of the party's council of advisers. bdnews24.co
